Guide.title: What is IPTV?
Guide.Content: It is a method used by some operators to allow you to access their online television package.A way of transmitting television over the Internet with a different method than that used by conventional streaming platforms.

Guide.title: What are IPTV channel lists?
Guide.Content: These are lists in which the addresses are stored with which the broadcasts of the IPTV channels can be accessed through remote IP addresses. The format that they usually have to reproduce is m3u.With these lists you can access the content sent by the operators to their customers, which allow you to access different channels from your mobile and without a decoder.
